'''Abbichu Oromo''' are one of the Tulema sub clans who live in [[North Shewa Zone (Amhara)|Semen Shewa]] zone in [[Ethiopia]]. In 1841 William Harris mentioned them as allies of King [[Sahle Selassie|Sahle Silassie]] of Shewa. The prominent settlements and towns are Lami, [[Meniida|Mendida]], Jiru, Robe, Deneba, Enewari and Chacha.

== History ==
The [[Commander-in-chief|commander in chief]] of his army, Ayto Mirach, was from this clan. At that time they inhabited the land north of Galan tribe, South of [[Menz]], west of Karayyu and east of [[Merhabete|Marhabiete]]. They became Christian in the 1830s, thus connecting the two [[Amhara people|Amhara]] dominions. The capital city of the tribe was Angolala. This tribe of [[Oromo language|Oromo]] were [[Amharic]] speakers and their territory joined the Amhara region. 
