'''Delele''' is a [[Zimbabwe]]an, [[Zambia]]n and north-eastern [[Botswana]] dish made from a local plant of the same name, and often eaten with [[sadza]] or [[Pap (food)|phaletšhe]]. The English word for delele is [[Okra]].<ref name="ZMOF"/> Okra is also referred to as "derere".<ref name="ZMOF"/><ref name="Dutiro Howard 2007 p. 93"/> It is prepared with [[baking soda]] and well known for its slimy texture. Delele can be dried before cooking, but more frequently it is cooked fresh.{{cn|date=December 2017}}

