'''''Demain à Nanguila ''''' (or ''Nanguila Tomorrow'') is a 1969 [[Cinema of Mali|Malian film]].
== Synopsis == ''Nanguila Tomorrow'' follows the steps of a young [[Mali]]an man while illustrating the detrimental effects of [[rural exodus]]. The film also questions the government’s decisions immediately after obtaining [[History of Mali|independence]] in its attempt to put a stop to the wave of people [[immigration|immigrating]] to the cities and to develop the country based on [[agriculture]]. A portrait of Mali in the 1960's by means of the [[nightlife]] in [[Bamako]], the capital’s monuments, and women bent under the weight of too many tasks, Nanguila Tomorrow is regarded as the first Malian [[movie|film]].{{citation needed|date=April 2012}}
